text: Thryptomene wannooensis is a shrub species in the family Myrtaceae that is endemic to Western Australia. The shrub is found in the Gascoyne region of Western Australia near Shark Bay. ==References== wannooensis Category:Endemic flora of Western Australia Category:Rosids of Western Australia Category:Endangered flora of Australia Category:Plants described in 2014 Category:Taxa named by Barbara Lynette Rye
